<div class="faq">
<details class="faq-item">
<summary>Does this collect any of my browsing data?</summary>
<p>No. The extension requests zero permissions beyond what's needed to open its own bundled files. It cannot see your open tabs, your browsing history, cookies, or anything on any page you visit. It only opens local HTML files when you click a report.</p>
</details>
<details class="faq-item">
<summary>Does it work on any page, or only in VinSolutions?</summary>
<p>It works from any tab in Chrome — VinSolutions, vAuto, Xtime, Dealertrack, a news article, wherever. The toolbar icon is always present. Click it from anywhere to open the launcher.</p>
</details>
<details class="faq-item">
<summary>Will it slow down my browser?</summary>
<p>No. The extension is a Manifest V3 extension with a lightweight service worker. It does nothing in the background — it only activates when you click the icon. It has no impact on page load times or browser performance.</p>
</details>
<details class="faq-item">
<summary>What size does the popup open at?</summary>
<p>Reports open in a dedicated 1200×800 pixel popup window. This is intentionally larger than a standard browser popup to give infographics and interactive tools proper breathing room, while still leaving your main tab visible behind it.</p>
</details>
<details class="faq-item">
<summary>Do I need admin rights or IT approval to install?</summary>
<p>In most cases, no. Installing Chrome extensions from the Web Store is a standard user action that doesn't require elevated permissions. However, if your organization uses Chrome managed policies, check with IT. The extension is published on the official Chrome Web Store, which makes it easier to whitelist if needed.</p>
</details>
<details class="faq-item">
<summary>Can I use this on my personal laptop or home computer?</summary>
<p>Yes. As long as you have Google Chrome installed, you can add the extension to any Chrome instance. Your Chrome profile syncs extensions, so if you're signed into Chrome on multiple devices, it may appear on all of them automatically.</p>
</details>
<details class="faq-item">
<summary>The Cox Integrations brand cards aren't responding — what's wrong?</summary>
<p>Make sure you installed from the Chrome Web Store link, not from a locally-loaded older version. The interactive elements require the latest published version of the extension. If you loaded an older version manually (via "Load unpacked"), remove it and reinstall from the store link.</p>
</details>
</div>
</div>
