<!-- WHAT IT DOES -->
<section class="section" id="what">
<div class="section-header">
<div class="section-num">1</div>
<div class="section-title">What It Does</div>
</div>
<p class="prose">The nVision AMI Extension adds a collapsible sidebar to <strong>nvision.coxautoinc.com</strong>. It reads shopper demand and traffic data directly from the nVision interface as you navigate — so there's no switching windows, no re-typing numbers, and no risk of copying the wrong figure into a slide.</p>
<p class="prose">Think of it as a form-filler that watches your screen. You navigate to the right pages in nVision, click Capture at the right moments, and the extension stores everything it needs. Then, with one click, it opens a pre-populated document ready to present.</p>
<div class="what-grid">
<div class="what-card">
<div class="what-card-icon">📋</div>
<h4>Inventory CSV Analysis</h4>
<p>Drop a dealer's inventory export from vAuto and the extension automatically identifies the top 6 models by volume, aged units, and monthly profit opportunity.</p>
</div>
<div class="what-card">
<div class="what-card-icon">👥</div>
<h4>Shopper Demand Capture</h4>
<p>Reads Audience Explorer data for each top model — Total DMA Shoppers, Ready to Buy, Actively Shopping, and Casually Browsing counts — directly from the page DOM.</p>
</div>
<div class="what-card">
<div class="what-card-icon">📈</div>
<h4>Traffic Metrics Capture</h4>
<p>Automates the multi-step process of capturing All Traffic and EO-filtered traffic from the Analyze Traffic report, including toggling Advanced Settings.</p>
</div>
<div class="what-card">
<div class="what-card-icon">📄</div>
<h4>Document Auto-Fill</h4>
<p>Launches the AMI One-Sheet, 10-Page Report, and Performance Report pre-loaded with everything captured — dealer name, efficiency, shopper counts, and traffic metrics.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="callout callout-info" style="margin-top:20px">
<span class="callout-icon">ℹ️</span>
<div><strong>No data leaves your browser.</strong> All captured data is stored in <code>chrome.storage.local</code> — it stays on your machine, persists between page navigations, and is cleared only when you click a Clear button or uninstall the extension.</div>
</div>
</section>
<!-- INSTALLATION -->
<section class="section" id="install">
<div class="section-header">
<div class="section-num">2</div>
<div class="section-title">Installation</div>
</div>
<p class="prose">This extension is installed manually in Developer Mode — it is not published to the Chrome Web Store. You will need the <code>.zip</code> file provided by your team.</p>
<ol class="install-steps">
<li class="install-step">
<div class="step-num">1</div>
<div class="step-content">
<h4>Unzip the extension package</h4>
<p>Extract <code>nvision-ami-extension-v3.zip</code> to a permanent folder on your computer — somewhere you won't accidentally delete it, like <code>Documents/Chrome Extensions/nVision AMI</code>. The extension loads from this folder while it's running, so it must stay in place.</p>
</div>
</li>
<li class="install-step">
<div class="step-num">2</div>
<div class="step-content">
<h4>Open Chrome Extensions</h4>
<p>In Chrome, navigate to <code>chrome://extensions</code> — or open the Chrome menu (⋮), go to <strong>Extensions → Manage Extensions</strong>.</p>
</div>
</li>
<li class="install-step">
<div class="step-num">3</div>
<div class="step-content">
<h4>Enable Developer Mode</h4>
<p>Toggle the <strong>Developer mode</strong> switch in the upper-right corner of the Extensions page. New buttons will appear at the top left.</p>
</div>
</li>
<li class="install-step">
<div class="step-num">4</div>
<div class="step-content">
<h4>Load the extension folder</h4>
<p>Click <strong>Load unpacked</strong>, then navigate to and select the folder you unzipped in Step 1 — the folder that contains <code>manifest.json</code>. Click <strong>Select Folder</strong>.</p>
</div>
</li>
<li class="install-step">
<div class="step-num">5</div>
<div class="step-content">
<h4>Confirm it's active</h4>
<p>You should see <strong>nVision AMI Extension</strong> appear in your list with a blue toggle. Navigate to <code>nvision.coxautoinc.com</code> — a collapsed sidebar labeled <strong>AMI</strong> will appear on the right edge of the screen.</p>
</div>
</li>
</ol>
<div class="callout callout-warn">
<span class="callout-icon">⚠️</span>
<div><strong>Never move or rename the unzipped folder</strong> after loading the extension. Chrome references the original folder location — if the folder moves, the extension will show an error and need to be reloaded.</div>
</div>
</section>
