<div class="workflow">
<!-- Dealer Info -->
<div class="workflow-step">
<div class="workflow-badge badge-launch" style="background:#374151">D</div>
<div class="workflow-card">
<h3>Before You Start — Enter Dealer Information</h3>
<p>At the top of the sidebar, enter the dealer name, New Vehicle Efficiency %, and Used Vehicle Efficiency %. Click <strong>Save Dealer Info</strong>.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Dealer Name</strong> — the extension attempts to auto-detect this from the nVision page header. Verify it's correct.</li>
<li><strong>New/Used Efficiency %</strong> — these are sourced from the dealer's ProfitTime GPS data or AMI dashboard.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<!-- Step 1 -->
<div class="workflow-step">
<div class="workflow-badge badge-step1">S1</div>
<div class="workflow-card">
<h3>Step 1 — Drop the Inventory CSV</h3>
<p>Export the dealer's current inventory from vAuto as a CSV file. Then drag and drop it onto the blue drop zone in the sidebar, or click the zone to browse for the file.</p>
<ul>
<li>The extension parses the CSV to identify the <strong>top 6 models by volume</strong>.</li>
<li>Results display instantly: Active New count, average ProfitTime score, and a breakdown of Critical / Moderate / Healthy units.</li>
<li>Each model shows aged 60+ units and estimated monthly profit opportunity.</li>
<li>These 6 models become the capture targets for Step 2.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<!-- Step 2 -->
<div class="workflow-step">
<div class="workflow-badge badge-step2">S2</div>
<div class="workflow-card">
<h3>Step 2 — Capture Shopper Data for Each Model</h3>
<p>Navigate to the <strong>Audience Explorer</strong> page in nVision. The sidebar will display the 6 models from your CSV, with an arrow pointing at the current model to capture.</p>
<ul>
<li>In nVision, set the Make/Model filter to the highlighted model, then click <strong>Apply</strong>.</li>
<li>Once the Audience Explorer data loads, click <strong>Capture: [Model Name]</strong> in the sidebar.</li>
<li>The extension reads Total DMA Shoppers, Ready to Buy, Actively Shopping, and Casually Browsing from the page.</li>
<li>A green checkmark confirms capture. The arrow advances to the next model automatically.</li>
<li>Repeat for all 6 models. Click a captured model's <strong>↻</strong> icon to re-capture if needed.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<!-- Step 3 -->
<div class="workflow-step">
<div class="workflow-badge badge-step3">S3</div>
<div class="workflow-card">
<h3>Step 3 — Capture Traffic Data</h3>
<p>Navigate to the <strong>Analyze Traffic</strong> page in nVision. The Capture Traffic Metrics button will activate once you're on the right page.</p>
